<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium marchicum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marchicum">Microthecium marchicum</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its ostiolate ascomata and citrifrom, smooth-walled ascospores. Its ascospores are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. geoporae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="geoporae">Mi. geoporae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. hypomyces" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hypomyces">Mi. hypomyces</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. levitum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="levitum">Mi. levitum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. zobelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="zobelii">Mi. zobelii</taxonomicName>
, but all of them produce non-ostiolate ascomata.
</paragraph>
